caption: Got food poisoning. After I ate, about an hour went by, and I felt exhausted. Upon laying down and a wave of nausea hit as if I was drunk, yet I haven't had a drink in 4 years. I puked, barely made it to the toilet..cross contaimination maybe? Never again...

Top Indian food! I’m a local that has ordered from here for years. The food is delicious, the dining experience lacks ambience but it’s BYOB so that evens everything out. I’m a huge fan of the chicken Saag. Has kept me coming back for years.
The food is very flavorful and leads me to keep going back!

Food and service was top quality . Unlike any  other Indian restaurants I have ever visited in the US. ( atleast in the My experience) Looking for great quality ,real Indian food .& Goat Biryani lovers  This is the place .  Great food 🥃🥃👍

Called the restaurant when my food was 20 min late and was told the delivery guy left 5 min ago.  Then had a missed call 4 min later and called back 5 min after that. Person on the phone tells me the delivery guy had actually delivered that food a while ago. (I had asked for contactless delivery and to be texted when food is dropped off) I open my front door - nothing there. I tell the guy that I don’t know where that food is delivered, but it’s not here, and now I don’t want it because I don’t know where it has been and I don’t want cold food. They tell me I’m they Can’t refund my money without returning the food. Obviously, this is a problem. I don’t have the food so I can’t return it. I ask him to have the delivery driver go to the address he delivered to and then call me and we can all get on the phone together and that should be enough to show it was delivered to the wrong Address. I have yet to hear back from them (an apology would be nice) and had to threaten to contest the charge because the manager wouldn’t authorize a refund without the food returned. I understand that mistakes happen, but I’m not a thief, and I am not trying to get free food. I believe I came up with a constructive way to prove it was delivered to the wrong address but was just ignored and left hungry. Also I would like to note that this restaurant uses their own delivery drivers so contacting them is Not a problem. The reason for 2 stars and not 1 is because I do believe it was an honest mistake  but again, I can’t recommend a restaurant when I have received service like this.  I hope this was a one time experience and that if you do decide to order from here, you’re not Subject to the same experience.

We enjoy to go out. Last night we arrived in this fine restaurant which friends told us about. We spent a beautiful experience there with first-rate food and a professional crew and a talented cook. We put this place in our list  and we shall definitely go again very soon.  Highly recommended.
we order from this place every week! the food is great and they always deliver on time or earlier. i love the kali daal, paneer makhni and gulab jamun :)
The chicken Biriyani is a scam. . . It's just chicken Tikka masala mixed with overcooked basmati rice.   No dry fruits. . No spices. . Nothing. . . 😣😣

Worst customer service. I had ordered Aaloo parantha and aaloo tiki. Tikki was kinda ok. The parantha had no filling inside. When I called them up to tell about my experience,  I was told this is how they make it. According to them , they had stuffed mashed potatoes,  I think I know how mashed potatoes taste like. But there was only the flour part.  I get it somedays might not be good. A polite acceptance goes a long way
I placed my order at 6:08 and it delivered at 7:32. Unless you're not hungry and happy to wait.

When I order Chili Chicken, I expect battered or fried piece of chicken, in a spicy sauce. What I got was strips of chicken that have been simmered in a tomato sauce. Sorry, the price of $14 and the modest portion size and the incorrect preparation means I won't go back for this. A shame, as the mint sauce was great.

Awful experience!! We found a roach in our lamb pasanda!!  , first time we had this experience.. it is so sad because we used to like the food but the pasanda was old , the oil was separated from the sauce plus the delivery guy refused to enter the building because there is alot of movement, we have 3 elevators so that’s a terrible excuse to not want to come up . The restaurant refuses to give us a full refund for the whole order but who will want to eat the other plates if their food looks old plus there is a roach!

This is a pseudo-indian. I have tried Indians  hundreds of times in my life, and never been so disappointed as this one. We ordered three different curries and a naan. The Naan was terrible - it was similar to the one from any supermarket. About curries, it's a bit more subtle.. out of millions of spices that would make the food tasty, the chef in this restaurant chooses to use a single one, sugar. We have read through past reviews, and decided to order curries with less sugar. We did not know at that moment it means no taste. This restaurant does not know a thing about the Indian food. Whoever thinks how bad an Indian curry can go and anyway order from here will certainly broaden their perspectives on food, by setting the lowest boundary of their  food history throughout life, at least under the Indian category.

I go to this outstanding restaurant every couple of days  as I love the special air that is outline this place. The personel is exceptionally cordial and qualified. The service is certainly fast. Also, the food you get is good. I frequent often and I was always joyful. The payment is reasobable. I highly suggest this restaurant to to all.
(Translated by Google) Delicious food  (Original) Deliciosa la comida
This place offers wonderful service and delightful meals. My favourite restaurant in the city. The food served fast and the prices are economical. Will definitely recommend this spot.
One of my main places to grab something to eat. excellent location, well kept, and good service. 5 stars!
One of the best tasting Indian food I’ve had, apply on what I usually order ( chicken tikka massala)
Great chicken tikka masala and chicken samosas.
The food has ZERO flavor, NO SPICES, and is all around a HUGE disappointment. The Chana Masala tastes like chickpeas in Chef Boyardee sauce. :( :( :(
Prices kinda high

Last week was the first time we went to this magnificent restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We enjoyed the evening a lot with the courteous service, with the exceptional  dishes and wine and with the modest pay. We will no doubt come back soon.
The food is always well prepared and tasty, employees hands out excellent customer service. I love the cleanliness and character. Will visit here again.
The place offers a great variety of delicious food. I enjoy eating here. Staff members are always friendly, rates are convenient and the place is always clean.
The service is regularly swift, good mood, very nice employees. I will return here again when I get nearby.
Just ok

Service was good, fish curry not that good, had like four little pieces of fish with lot of onions.
Had to call three times to get my small order delivered two hours after I had placed my order, despite living not far from the restaurant.
Had the Tandoori vegetables.  It was okay, nothing I'd order again. It's close by but I rarely eat there.  I wouldn't tell anyone it's great,  just okay.
Their chicken Tika massala tastes delicious. The fact that it feels freshly made adds to my satisfaction each time.
Lied about food being delivered, best around the bush for 2 hours. Managed by bad people.
Standard Indian nothing special

Ok food. Reasonably priced lunch. Ok service. Mulligatawny blah. Garlic naan delicious. Kebab platter appetizer nice portion for lunch. Maybe a second try?
This food from Maharaja Palace is amazing! The food is delicious and flavorful! It’s my go to spot when Im in Harlem and craving good Indian food.

We didn’t like any of the 4 things we ordered, and couldn’t eat the rice because it was delivered in non-heat-resistant plastic containers. I wish the food was seasoned better, and that the papadams weren’t too salty. Food felt pretty fresh tho and portions were generous.
Good price. Portions seem a little on the lower side, but realized it is is just right. Food is good. We were here on a Sunday evening- Service was good as well. Will most likely come back.
Their staff is  rude  if you dont k ow how to talk.please close the business and go home i called for delivery and they just rude

I would have given 3 stars but I had a really poor delivery experience. Food took nearly 2 hours, double the 35-55 minute range given when ordered. When we finally received the food we found that an order of naan was missing. The chicken tikka masala wasn't bad but it was obvious the chicken wasn't grilled first. The dish was missing the complexities which generally make it so good. The kali daal was very good with a little spiciness and a great flavor. Based on the food I might consider ordering from them again but because of the issues with delivery and the missing item I'll order from elsewhere in the future.

I almost never write reviews for places, but the food here was simply terrible.  The dahl was undercooked, devoid of flavor, and half full of kidney beans, which was bizzare.  The baghare baigan (an eggplant dish) was slightly better, but that's not really a complement.  What flavor it did have was way off.   Honestly, it didn't even taste like Indian food.  The roti was extremely tough and hard to chew.   Oh, and the delivery was over an hour late.  The only positive thing I can say about this place was the papadum.  Again, this is my first google review in years, and I'm having trouble describing just how disappointing this food was.  I love Indian food, and I'm generally of the mind that even bad Indian food is good, but not this place.  If you're in the mood for Indian, find somwhere else.

Food was tasteless and bland.  They seem to water down everything from the appetizers to the soup.  I had the mulligatawny soup.  It tasted like water with food coloring in it.  Dishes also tasted like they just threw water in a pan with some ingredients and added some coloring for presentation.  I would not recommend this place for indian.  Go downtown to little india where they care about the customers…and season the food for a complete dining experience😩🤔☹️😳
Food is terrible. I asked for 2 Roti and got burnt pita bread instead.

The manager is Racist and completely baised, Expected great food but its just ok, when said to go for the meal they take in and give you just 1/3 of the total portion and charge you full money. Bloody cheats, I do not recommend this place at all.
My favorite Indian delivery spot, bar none.

Maharaja Palace is a very nice and affordable Indian restaurant in the central Harlem area.  I have tried all their chicken and lamb entrees and each one of them has a different flavor and spice profile.  Anybody craving Indian curries should surely order from this place. Entrees are cheap and everything costs below $15.  They should really come up with weekend lunch buffet like other Indian restaurants in the city!

Usually better but today something seemed to be off. They didn't pick up the phone so I went there in person since they usually are quick. Today not so much. Took a long time. The tandoori chicken had little meat and it took about 40 min to prepare the order. Still ok based on past experience.
I prefer ordering takeout or delivery from here. It is a restaurant but the ambiance isn't fine dining. It is just a regular restaurant. The food is good though.
great place

Food tastes authentic and great. But the quantity is "way too" less for the price. There is no buffet. All these explains why the place is without any crowd even in the lunch time. The front reception lady received us well, but the other guy who i think is the manager was rude to us when we asked him to share the food for us. Overall, definitely would not recommend this place when you are hungry. Because you'll end up spending a whole lot.
Great food, good portions, and great service.

Ate inside, there was noone there but us, thus service was good. All 3 dishes were excellent (chicken Tikka, fish, Peas..don't recall names). Serving bowls are nice as they keep food warm. free crusty bread/dipping sauces also good. I'll be back.
Tikka masala was a bit watery than what I’m used to.
i love this food ...grat delivery.

This is one of my go-to Indian restaurants certainly the best in Harlem the food is always fresh I noticed one of the other reviews and had the same experience the first time I asked for the food to be spicy it was not very spicy the second time I reminded them of this and said I really want an It,spicy and it was fantastic just the right hot and each time I go they remember me and Cook it  the same way. My wife orders the Chicken Tikka Masala and always loves it. I tend to stick with the lamb Curry's my favorite is the Lamb  Shashlik. The naan bread is always delicious slightly crispy and tender inside and for dessert I often get the Rasmalai. The prices are not cheap but the portions are large the food is fresh it is very difficult to find inexpensive quality food in New York City but it is certainly not pricey. My favorite waiter is Sumon not sure if I'm spelling it right wonderful guy always has a smile on his face.
Great food, great service, affordable price. Great place overall!

We found a sharp, 1 cm long, cone-shaped piece of plastic in the palak paneer. Called the restaurant and texted them an image. The manager we spoke to told me that nothing like that is in their facilities, accusing me of making it up so I could have a refund. He also told me plastic has to be black or white, and this particular piece had a green tint (It was in the palak paneer). He was extremely rude. Never ordering from here again.

Ok, so there are a LOT of highly regarded restaurants in this neighborhood. My wife and I were walking around one night and were getting tired of hearing about long waits at some of the other places we had picked out.  We gave up and went to Maharaja, thinking that it was gonna be so-so Indian food. It REALLY surprised us. Super tasty Naan and Chicken Tikka Masala and LOVED the samosas!
Very welcoming, friendly staff. Fantastic Indian food with a strong variety of dishes. Probably my favorite Indian food in NY.

The people are so nice and the food is so good!!  I am very happy to have this place in the neighborhood.  Quick delivery, great service in the restaurant and may I mention the food again??  I love exploring their menu, haven't found a dish I don't like yet!

Very good! I'm a vegetarian and ordered Methi Malai Mutter with paneer, with garlic naan. It was amazing! Loved the food! So delicious!

My son and I love this place. Lamb dishes are delicious. Some of the best saag I've ever had. And the service is friendly. But bring your own beer our wine, at least for now.
